Udis86 (Minimalistic x86 disassembler library)

Udis86 is a  disassembler for the x86  and  x86-64 class  of
instruction  set architectures.  It consists of a  C library
called libudis86 which provides a clean and simple interface
to  decode a stream  of raw binary data,  and to inspect the
disassembled instructions in a structured manner.

https://github.com/vmt/udis86